title: 50 Modern American and British Poets 1920-1970 (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
McKay | 1973 | Pdf | Eng | 358 pages | 32.5 MB

The poets represented in this anthology, from Robert Frost to Erica Jong, have captured in their work the living portrait of changes in style and sensibility from 194O to 1970. These fifty years have given us a range and diversity of voices and imaginations scarcely realized in any age. It is also fitting that this rich harvest of poetry comes almost fifty years after Louis Untermeyer's original landmark anthology of British and American poetry, a book which has been a basic experience for millions of American readers
